net.java.jddac.jmdi.fblock
Class EchoBlock

java.lang.Object
  net.java.jddac.common.fblock.Entity
      net.java.jddac.jmdi.fblock.FunctionBlock
          net.java.jddac.jmdi.fblock.EchoBlock
All Implemented Interfaces:
ConfigurationInterface, SubscriberCallback
public class EchoBlock
extends FunctionBlock
implements SubscriberCallback

This function block subscribes to a publication topic and publishes on a second topic. When it receives a publication, it echoes whatever it receives to the screen. Provides following services: OpIdSubscribe [9216] - A probe subscribing to a topic. In: (0) String - NCAP ID of Probe. (1) String - Publicatioon Topic. Out: None OpIdUnsubscribe [9217] - A probe unsubscribing to a topic. In: (0) String - NCAP ID of Probe. (1) String - Publicatioon Topic. Out: None Required varibles that specify Publication Topics: None. Required varibles that specify Subscription Topics: None. Required variables that specify object tags of required F-Blocks: MessageQueueTag - ObjectTag for a F-FunctionBlock of type MessageQueue. Required other variables: None.

configure

public void configure(ArgArray configuration)
               throws java.lang.Exception
Description copied from interface: ConfigurationInterface
Provides a method to configure object properties. The registry argument contains an ArgArray composed named values. Any values that are not specified are assumed to be left unchanged. That is, if a value is not present, do not assume it means 0 or true or some other default. This allows the configure method to be used to set a single value without affecting other values.
